		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Spell and AA ideas</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>Since it looks like a new expansion that raises levels is coming, that will mean lots more spells and AA are needed, so I thought I would start a thread for people to post ideas on.<br />
<br />
Please keep this thread on topic, I'll delete comments that aren't useful.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Sarsi Solverna</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">April 10th, 2006 08:45 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I've always thought that they should consider extending the differences between the elements when they came out with the damage flappys.  And especially now since they came out with Pyromancy.<br />
<br />
Perhaps they could introduce some competing abilitys to Pyromancy:<br />
<br />
For Pyromancy, there's a chance to cause more damage via the fire dot.<br />
<br />
Perhaps for cold there could be a chance to slow a monsters attack speed, or snare or root <br />
<br />
For magic, it could be a short stun effect.<br />
<br />
Personally, I'd like to see them revise the flappys somewhat, so that you can focus on specilializing more to an element and don't feel like you need to be constantly switching between the different varieties.  Perhaps where the 2nd rank of a particular flappy would give the first rank boost of the other elemental varieties, and so on.  I'd rather they get rid of the mana regen line of flappys completely and apply the respective mana regen bonuses to each rank of the elemental flappy's.<br />
<br />
Sarsi Solverna<br />
Valiant Crusaders<br />
The Tribunal</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
