<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Looseal</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">April 10th, 2006 08:53 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>1) Please give us a prismatic focus flappy with some decent mana regen. - even a mana-expensive spell rather than AA would be acceptable.<br />
<br />
2) It's been asked for before, but some MGB TL capabilities would be nice.<br />
<br />
3) An AA or spell that lets the wizard port his group to his secondary bind would be SO cool.<br />
<br />
4) A single-target, long-duration snare is long overdue.<br />
<br />
5) Group-based improved invis.<br />
<br />
6) A cool magic nuke along the lines of Chaos Flame or Claw of Vox to make magic nukes more viable than they currently are.  Chaos Flame is incredibly nice because it's an excellent complement to Pyromancy.  CoV is nice because it's incredibly efficient.  There's rarely, if ever a good reason to cast magic nukes.<br />
<br />
7) Gadget spell: I'd really like to see a spell that's fast-casting, fast refresh that would blip a wizard a fixed distance (say 200) feet at a time along the lines of shadow step, but this one would accelerate the wizard in the direction he's already facing.  It would be a kind of warp to complement a wizard's mastery of travel through time and space.  Normal restrictions apply: must stay on Z axis, can't warp through walls, etc.  It would be fun to use this in places like the Karanas where the distances are entirely too long.<br />
<br />
8) AA &quot;Meditative Mastery&quot;; 5 levels; 5/5/5/5/5:  Each level obtained in Meditative Mastery will allow a wizard who is standing still to gain 20% of his meditation skill as though he were sitting.<br />
  - this would go a long way in addressing the fact that wizards are the most sensitive class in the game where it comes to mana availability in areas where horses aren't permitted.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
