		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Xien</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">April 11th, 2006 09:55 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Harvest Extension:<br />
<br />
How about a Harvest like ability or spell that works something like a reverse mana dot.  So, say 250 mana to cast, and the longer it's on the more mana you recieve, start small and increase, kind of like the progressive dots on the Shaman and Druid 1.0 epics.  make it just pay for the 250 mana over the first 3 - 4 ticks, but the longer it lasts, the more mana you get.  Also make it like Scale of the Wolf where if you get hit, it drops.  Also make it so that if you cast it drops.  This way it would prevent us from having some form of limitless mana while in combat, but give us a reasonable way to fill back up the tank without waiting for 7-10 minutes.<br />
<br />
<br />
Chaotic Stun<br />
<br />
A random duration stun 1 - 30 seconds would be fun.  <br />
<br />
<br />
Snare<br />
<br />
This spell line has been neglected for far too long.  Wizards are expected to snare in groups, why can't we get something that lasts a while or has a better resist modifier or is a single target snare?  I had one of the zone in goblins in Stillmoon resist snare EIGHT snare casts this morning.  That's just wrong.<br />
<br />
<br />
Summoning Mobs,<br />
<br />
There are few, if any classes as impacted by this game mechanic as Wizards.  Weak in the armor/hp department, no DA ability, no pet to depend on for agro and DPS, no healing capabilities.  If it summons our stuns likely won't stick.  Soloing Summoning mobs worth soloing is out of the question, unlike almost every other class.  In a group situation it changes the amount of burn we can put down before we are in mortal danger.  Somewhere along the line most mobs that a group will be doing moved to being a summoning mobs.  An anti summoning Aura, or short duration quick casting long recast spell that you could drop prior to going into a burn mode, a lure based stun or two, something to give us the ability to really go all out when called for.  Anyone ever remember stealing agro in a positive way back in the day?  <br />
<br />
Healer is lom, tank is getting low, you're in full burn, the mob starts walking at you instead of finishing of the tank who isn't going to get a heal for another 10 seconds.  Those were fun, exciting and important capabilities we lost when group mobs became summoning mobs.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
