		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div><b>Spellcasting Overhaste</b><br />
A one minute duration group buff which acts to supplement the current line of cleric spellhaste spells.<br />
It would work to do so by reducing the recast timer by a percentage (25%) for spells <i>where recast timer is less than 180</i>.<br />
<br />
A buff like this is great for two reasons. It would be highly coveted by wizards wanting to do better burst dps. And it would also be highly coveted by all casters, healers, knights, caster dps as well. <br />
<br />
So this gives us utility and yet remains focused on improving our damage capability.<br />
<br />
Standard recast is 2.25 secs. with 25% recast lowered that comes down to 1.6875secs. Heals come sooner. Dps goes up.<br />
<br />
DPS on Ancient Core Fire chained.<br />
If someone's regular setup has them casting acf in 5.5 secs unfocused <br />
With  0% recast reduction, we're getting 525 dps.<br />
With 20% recast reduction, that's up to 558 dps.<br />
With 25% recast reduction, that's up to 566 dps.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Alikat Astrae</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">May 17th, 2006 08:42 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>An idea I had, reposted from a discussion in another topic thread:<br />
<br />
How about a Wizard gets a nuke that does 500 DD. When cast, it places a buff in the target's buff box that indicates &quot;Level One&quot; of that spell. Next time the Wizard casts the same DD spell, it does 1K DD, and the buff is overwritten with a buff indicating &quot;Level Two&quot; of that spell. If the target has the Level Two icon and is hit by the same spell, it does 2K DD and the buff is overwritten with a &quot;Level Three&quot; icon. Put in five levels, and the spell would do up to 16K per nuke, but no crit capacity or focus will work (like the old dragon/giantbane nukes). Or four levels for up to 8K per nuke, but with the normal crit/focus capacity. At max level, the buff would become ablative, meaning it would fade after being nuked with that same spell.<br />
<br />
That would allow Wizards to nuke for high damage, low mana on raids, but without infinite stackability, since they would not each get their own buff icon, but would be overwriting for each other on a single buff icon. It would take a single Wizard multiple casts to ramp the buff up, and the final buff icon would not be over-writable, but would fade after being hit with again at max level, requiring another ramp-up. Raiding Wizards would like doing loads of DPS for low mana costs, and grouping Wizards would like doing large nukes for moderate mana costs (the nuke itself, which would do 500 DD at Level Zero, would be around 250 mana per cast, which would become as efficient as CoF at Level One, subsequent levels would bring the mana cost down well below that of CoV). In group settings, the more hitpoints/longer fight times per mob, better this nuke would be. In raid settings, the Wizzies could coordinate to use the tactic of timing their nukes so that they ramped the level up to maximum as quickly as possible.<br />
<br />
That would give Wizzies a finitely-stackable instant DD line that could be high-damage/high-efficiency, but would not be immediately overpowering, and the finite stackability would favor raiding parties with five Wizards per raid, though fewer or more Wizards would still be able to use it, just not at peak efficiency. That would make Wizards desirable but not in large numbers like the current DD model.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
